b'Per our Civic Integrity policy (https://t.co/uQ0AoPtoCm), the tweets yesterday may mislead people into thinking they don\xe2\x80\x99t need to register to get a ballot (only registered voters receive ballots). We\xe2\x80\x99re updating the link on @realDonaldTrump\xe2\x80\x99s tweet to make this more clear.'

b'This does not make us an \xe2\x80\x9carbiter of truth.\xe2\x80\x9d Our intention is to connect the dots of conflicting statements and show the information in dispute so people can judge for themselves. More transparency from us is critical so folks can clearly see the why behind our actions.'

b'Fact check: there is someone ultimately accountable for our actions as a company, and that\xe2\x80\x99s me. Please leave our employees out of this. We\xe2\x80\x99ll continue to point out incorrect or disputed information about elections globally. And we will admit to and own any mistakes we make.'
